<p><b>Freedom of thought</b> (also called <b>freedom of conscience</b> and <b>freedom of ideas</b>) is the <a href="/wiki/Freedom_(political)" title="Freedom (political)" class="mw-redirect">freedom</a> of an individual to hold or consider a fact, viewpoint, or <a href="/wiki/Thought" title="Thought">thought</a>, independent of others' viewpoints. It is closely related to, yet distinct from, the concept of <a href="/wiki/Freedom_of_speech" title="Freedom of speech">freedom of expression</a>.</p>
<table id="toc" class="toc" summary="Contents">
